Hmm, so the "status" column is the one of interest correct?

Maybe the parser needs to be set as "text" instead of "numeric" because the values are strings and aren't parsed.

```js
$.tablesorter.addParser({ 
    // set a unique id 
    id: 'status',
    is: function(s) {
        // return true so this parser is auto detected 
        return false; 
    },  
    format: function(s) { 
        // format your data for normalization 
        for(var i=0; i<getTypeList.length;i++){
            s = s.replace(getTypeList[i],i);
        }
        return s;
    }, 
    // set type, either numeric or text 
    type: 'text' 
});
```

