@ahopkins this is what I did for `_get_user_id`, I think it is "safer" regarding the description of the object that should be returned with the `authenticate` method:

```python
# in exceptions
@add_status_code(500)
class InvalidRetrieveUserObject(SanicJWTException):

    def __init__(
            self,
            message="The retrieve_user method should return either a dict or an object with a to_dict method."
    ):
        super().__init__(message)
```

```python
    def _get_user_id(self, user):
        if isinstance(user, dict):
            user_id = user.get(self.app.config.SANIC_JWT_USER_ID)
        elif hasattr(user, 'to_dict') and callable(user.to_dict):
            user_id = user.to_dict().get(self.app.config.SANIC_JWT_USER_ID)
        else:
            raise exceptions.InvalidRetrieveUserObject()
        return user_id
```

