Best to keep generated static files and your SCSS files separate because you don't want CSS files in your Git repo. So I would not set `SASS_PROCESSOR_ROOT` so that it defaults to `STATIC_ROOT`, django-sass-processor will automatically detect where it's at. We don't have some kind of `SASS_ROOT`, that might be for a different app though.

Also set the `SASS_PROCESSOR_INCLUDE_DIRS` to the `scss/` folder, otherwise you have to do the following in your SCSS files:
```sass
@import 'scss/something';
```

You have also set `STATICFILES_DIRS` to a list of directories that already are in `mysite/static/` so you don't need to include that in `sass_src`.

