I hope you managed to sign your urls, but if not (and for the sake of others ending up here) here's a hint:

I based my solution on the accepted answer from this [question on Stackoverflow](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2573919/creating-signed-urls-for-amazon-cloudfront) which pretty much works out of the box. I exchanged M2Crypto for [rsa](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/rsa) to get a pure Python implmentation.

@kyleknap, IOBase can certainly work with streaming data. This is sufficient for my current use-case, but with a little more work I think it could be fully supported. My main interest was in line-by-line iteration:

```python
class StreamingBodyIO(RawIOBase):
    """Wrap a boto StreamingBody in the IOBase API."""
    def __init__(self, body):
        self.body = body

    def readable(self):
        return True

    def read(self, n=-1):
        n = None if n < 0 else n
        return self.body.read(n)
```

